      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Those clichés \"it gets better\" and \"time heals everything\" can come across as insensitive, especially when they don't feel true to your experience. It's like they're implying that the pain will magically fade away, which isn't the case for you. Allow yourself to feel the weight of your grief – it's okay to acknowledge and process the pain. Remind yourself that your loved one's memory is still alive in you, and grief is a journey that's unique to you and your experiences.",
      "source": "target",
